<%#
  Override letter_opener_web's default styles to disable dark mode.

  letter_opener_web applies a CSS filter that inverts all colors when the OS
  is in dark mode. This mangles our carefully-designed MJML email previews
  (cream backgrounds turn black, purple turns yellow, etc.).

  This file shadows the gem's built-in partial at the same engine path.
  It renders the original styles first, then layers on a media query that
  neutralizes the dark-mode inversion so emails preview true-to-color.
%>
<style>
  <%= render file: LetterOpenerWeb::Engine.root.join("app/views/layouts/letter_opener_web/styles/_letters.html.erb") %>
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    body {
      background-color: white !important;
      color: black !important;
      filter: none !important;
    }
  }
</style>
